---
import '@fontsource/yuji-syuku';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Tail - Bonjiri';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} />
<main>
  <h1>Tail - <span>ぼんじり</span></h1>
  <p>
    Butt, tail, pope's nose. They all refer to the very fatty small triangular piece of meat at the
    tail end of the chicken. It's grilled so the skin is crispy, even so the flavor and fattiness
    burst when you bite down into the tiny pieces.
  </p>
</main>

<style>
  main {
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 75ch;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  h1 {
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  h1 span {
    font-family: 'Yuji Syuku', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
  }

  p {
    margin: 0;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
</style>
